parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear coil springs can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, including punctured tires and damaged struts.
symptoms: Loud clunking or banging noise
sagging rear end
popping noise when turning
and flat tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front coil springs can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, including punctured tires and damaged struts.
symptoms: Loud clunking or banging noise
sagging front end
and flat tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Suspension issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Wobbling or unstable vehicle
loud noise
and loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake issues can cause accidents and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Low brake pads
and brake failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Other issues can cause inconvenience and discomfort to the driver.
symptoms: Auto light switch failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal has excessive side-to-side movement
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the vehicle surges forward when applying the brake
the brake lights do not illuminate
the ABS light appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Adjustable Brake and Gas Pedal Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the adjustable brake and gas pedal system can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal has excessive side-to-side movement
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the vehicle surges forward when applying the brake
the brake lights do not illuminate
the ABS light appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light appears on the dashboard
the brake pedal pulsates when applying the brake
the vehicle skids or surges when applying the brake
the brake lights do not illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without warning
even when the accelerator pedal is not pressed
the vehicle surges forward
the engine RPM increases
and the vehicle may not respond to braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control failure can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control does not disengage
the vehicle accelerates without warning
the brakes may not respond
and the vehicle may not slow down even when the accelerator pedal is released.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Throttle cable failure can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The throttle cable becomes stuck or malfunctioning
causing the vehicle to accelerate without warning
the engine RPM increases
and the vehicle may not respond to braking.
